data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction can be replaced:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — simple lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery **will no longer compile** because `ExecuteUpdateAsync` now takes `Action<...>` instead of `Expression<Func<...>>`.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` columns will get a numeric suffix appended. A new migration will rename columns.

**b) Nested complex types use full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. Again, a migration will rename the column.

**Fix:** pin the old names explicitly so no rename migration is generated:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe output */ }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
